EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to protection of trees during construction.
EventItemMatterName: Protection of trees during construction.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting smoking in pedestrian plazas and public parks and to repeal subdivision b of section 17-513 of the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring a study regarding the prevention of second-hand smoke circulation in restaurants.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting smoking in pedestrian plazas and public parks.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the rate set by the Commissioners of the Board of Elections in the City of New York pursuant to Section 7-207(5) of the State Election Law to compensate party representatives for their time spent monitoring the preparation of voting machines and devices pursuant to Sections 7-207(2) and 7-207(3) of the State Election Law.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the rate set by the Commissioners of the Board of Elections in the City of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Governor and the New York State Legislature to take all appropriate actions to identify and close underutilized state prison facilities.
EventItemMatterName: Governor and the NYS Legislature to take all appropriate actions to identify and close underutilized state prison facilities.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to certificates of occupancy.
EventItemMatterName: Certificates of occupancy.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass A.11549, legislation which would amend the selection process for the Chancellor of Education in the City of New York by requiring that the Mayor obtain the advice and consent of the New York City Council when appointing a Chancellor.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the selection process for the Chancellor of Education in the City of NY.  (A.11549)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring pedicabs to be subject to parking rules.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring pedicabs to be subject to parking rules.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Legislature to pass Governor Patersonâ€™s Program Bill #252, authorizing the electronic recording of instruments affecting real property.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to pass Governor Patersonâ€™s Program Bill #252, authorizing the electronic recording of instruments affecting real property.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would require the dates for payment of the Metropolitan Commuter Transportation Mobility Tax to correspond with tax filing dates for the payment of federal and state income taxes.
EventItemMatterName: Require the dates for payment of the Metropolitan Commuter Transportation Mobility Tax to correspond with tax filing dates for the payment of federal and state income taxes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon USAID to work with the Pakistani-American community to direct relief to Pakistan through non-governmental organizations.
EventItemMatterName: USAID to work with the Pakistani-American community to direct relief to Pakistan through non-governmental organizations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the sustainable remediation of superfund or brownfield sites on which there are existing properties and developments.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the sustainable remediation of superfund or brownfield sites on which there are existing properties and developments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report the results of its inspections of potential housing for the homeless.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report the results of its inspections of potential housing for the homeless.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permissible parking of vehicles when alternate side of the street rules are in effect for purposes of street cleaning.
EventItemMatterName: Permissible parking of vehicles when alternate side of the street rules are in effect for purposes of street cleaning.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and adopt, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would authorize the City of New York to establish a Small Performance Venue Business Tax Credit.
EventItemMatterName: Authorize the city of New York to establish a Small Performance Venue Business Tax Credit.
